  "prompt": "How much does it cost to hire a tax consultant to help me manage my stock option grant?",
  "response": "The cost to hire a tax consultant can vary significantly based on several factors, including location, the complexity of your stock option grant, and the level of expertise of the consultant. On average, you might expect to pay anywhere from $100 to $400 per hour. Some consultants might offer a fixed fee for specific services, while others might have retainer agreements.\n\nFor complex or high-value stock option grants, it might be more common to see fees on the higher end of this range. It's recommended to get quotes from multiple consultants and consider their experience, reputation, and the scope of services they offer before making a decision. Make sure to also discuss any potential additional costs or fees upfront.",
